<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119816>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Tukunha minor sp. nov., holotype female. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view.Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate; Ovp: ovipositor." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5119816/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119824>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Tukunha pinimauna sp. nov., holotype female. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate; Ovp: ovipositor." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5119824/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119828>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Tukunha pinimauna sp. nov., female specimen alive." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5119828/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119822>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Tukunha minor sp. nov., left tegmina of female in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5119822/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119826>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Tukunha pinimauna sp. nov., left tegmina of female in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." ;
